Sandeep is designing some 3-sided spinners.

He is going to spin each spinner once.

**(a)** 
(a) Write a different number on each dotted line so that when the spinner is spun it is **impossible** that the spinner will land on a number greater than 9
(b) Write a different number on each dotted line so that when the spinner is spun it is **certain** that the spinner will land on a multiple of 10
**(b)**  The likelihood of an outcome is **evens**.

On the probability scale, mark with a cross (X) the probability of this outcome.

